<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Shadows of Luclin System Requirements</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=462606" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    The minimum system requirements for the upcoming expansion to EverQuest have been announced.  They are as follows:
<blockquote><b>
If you have a Intel P-3 or AMD Athlon processor, you'll be able to get away with any 16MB or better D3D capable 3D card. If you have a lesser processor, the tentative minimum spec is:
<br><br>
P-2 400
<br>
128MB Ram
<br>
Nvidia GeForce Card
<br>
Another 400MB or so of free HDD space.
<br><br>
The recommended system spec will be a P3 or Athalon[sic] Processor with a GeForce 2 or better video card and 256MB of RAM.
</b></blockquote>
The rest of the Shadows of Luclin FAQ can be found <a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/luclin/faq.jsp" target="_blank">here</a>.

		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
